        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Speaking of FD, here's how I expected it to work when I was a newbie:</P><P>Cast FD when you know you're in trouble... mob leaves you alone.  Now I can wait a few minutes for the mob to walk away, get up, and run like hell to a zone.</P><P><BR>Reality:</P><P>Cast FD:  Fizzle.  Cast again, fizzle.  Cast again, interrupted.  Cast again, the spell casts, but you have fallen to the ground.  Wait 8 seconds for spell to refresh (assuming you're still alive) and cast FD for the 5th time, you die, but the mob performs a check to see if he believes your FD, and 50% of the time, he does not.</P><P>This is a spell that Verant wishes they never included in the game.  Why?  Because it means that if it worked, necros wouldn't die so often.  Death = lost exp.  Lost exp = hours and hours of time to recover.  Hours and hours of time = more $ to VI.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
