        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> My concerns for the Necro class is thus-</P><P>Pathing in zones.  We have takne years of abuse and misconception from other classes for lack of 'pet control' due to poor pathing. Pets breaking mez is the Necro's fault 100%, but betterin from a to b should NOT take pet thu FGHI and J.</P><P>Pets do not get tougher after level 49.  They get special abilities but all the abilities come at major pet AC/HP costs.</P><P>If you dont want us to Solo from level 8 on, then give us valid grouping spells from 8 on.  Or at least give us some semi-decent DD spells.  I can not even begin to tell you haw frustrating it is that the only thing I can do to mobs 55+ is life tap. </P><P>Increase the Epic's range of effected target. There is no reason that the weapons EPIC ability should not be able to land on almost any monster out there.  Yes even named major encounters. Its an EPIC, it is the difinitive weapon of all, the pinacle, the crowning jewel of a necro's 'life' (or so the quest sure felt like it).</P><P>In an exp group or raid environment, 32 peopl eon one 57th mob generally takes 5 to 18 seconds per encounter.  So we can do a max of 1500ish dmg at level 60 in the 12 seconds.  Why would a raid want a necro?  We cant heal as well as even a Druid.  We cant offer general spells (DMF is now overwritten by Spirit of the Eagle).  Our AC/HP/ATK debuffs/buffs are too short lived.  We need something to add value to a group.  My suggestion is this-<BR>    Deadmans Party. Level 58. Cost Ruby.  Casts a deathpact on group.  If a member of the group dies they have a chance of instant retribution where they are instantly brought back up to 50% health and 50% mana (similar to Divine Intervention/Death Pact of the cleric line). Casting Time 15seconds. Durration 1h30m.</P><P><BR>-Kidney Beene, Lanys</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></f